parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the depressurization vents can cause a popping noise, which may be a minor annoyance but does not affect vehicle operation or safety.
symptoms: similar to popcorn popping in a microwave
coming from the rear of the interior near the tail lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine sputtering and jerking can cause loss of power, deceleration, and difficulty accelerating, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

The malfunction of the infotainment system, specifically Apple CarPlay and integrated navigation, can cause driver distraction, pose a safety risk, and diminish the usability and value of the vehicle.
symptoms: directs the driver to turn on non-existent roads
and causes distraction while attempting to turn where there are no turns available.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden disengagement of the Adaptive Cruise Control (ACC) can cause the vehicle to slow down unexpectedly, increasing the risk of rear-end collisions or accidents, especially when following other vehicles at high speeds.
symptoms: the navigation system provides inaccurate information
the Stop/Start system fails to function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended activation of the automatic braking system can cause the vehicle to slow down or stop suddenly, increasing the risk of rear-end collisions or accidents, especially on wet roads or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The automatic braking system engages without warning
the vehicle slows down or stops suddenly
the driver experiences a loss of control
the system activates in the absence of obstacles or hazards.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: In-Vehicle Navigation and GPS System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the in-vehicle navigation and GPS system can cause safety concerns, particularly when driver assistance features deactivate, and the vehicle's location is not accurately displayed, potentially leading to accidents or disorientation.

The failure of the backup camera can increase the risk of accidents, injuries, or fatalities, particularly when reversing, as the driver may not be able to see obstacles or pedestrians behind the vehicle.

The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to tighten around the occupant, potentially leading to injury or inability to breathe, and compromise the effectiveness of the seatbelt in the event of a crash or sudden stop.
symptoms: The seat belt continues to retract and tighten around the occupant even after being unbuckled
the seat belt gets tangled in the seat track
the seat belt becomes stuck and renders the seat inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design flaw of the seat belt component can cause the seat belt to get caught and render the seat inoperable, potentially compromising the safety of the occupants in the event of a crash or sudden stop.
symptoms: The seat belt gets easily tangled in the seat track
the seat belt becomes stuck and renders the seat inoperable
the seat belt requires removal by a technician to become functional again.
